#######################################################################
                              Build Notes
#######################################################################

Scheduler:  To build the scheduler, copy the following source files to
            the listed locations in MINIX 3.1.8:

            servers/sched/schedule.c
                    -> /usr/src/servers/sched/schedule.c

            servers/sched/schedproc.h
                    -> /usr/src/servers/sched/schedproc.h

            servers/pm/schedule.c -> /usr/src/servers/pm/schedule.c

            Then navigate to /usr/src/tools and run

                        "make install"

            to update the custom MINIX install.

            Alternatively, run copysched.sh to do these commands.


Scripts:    All scripts in the testing require bash 4 to run, so be
            sure to have that installed on the test machine. The
            buildscripts.sh requres adding execute permissions to run, which
            can be done in MINIX with the command:

                    chmod +x buildscripts.sh

            Following are descriptions of each script:

                buildscripts.sh:    Generates the testing programs
                                    and a noise-filled file for
                                    testing. Run this 1st.

                cpu1-4.sh:          Run cpu intensive tasks and print
                                    times. See comments in scripts for
                                    details on individhual details.

                cputest.c:          Source file for a cpu intensive
                                    program. This is built by the 1st
                                    script. 

                io1.sh:             Runs an I/O intensive program
                                    alongside a cpu intensive one for
                                    testing.

                iotest.c:           The suggested I/O intensive program
                                    source code. Built by 1st script.



            







